--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Ubuntu Setup Scripts
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Version

I. Description

	A shell script, used to install and configure various applications and
	settings on a freshly installed Ubuntu server.

	The script has three sections:

	1.	Settings are used to customise the installation/administration process
	2.	Core functions are used to install various parts of the server
	3.	Admin function are used post-installation for maintenance
	
	The setting file and core file are combined to provided installation script
	functionality.
	
II. File list

	1. 	setting.sh: customises the installation/adminstration funtions (user configurable)
	2. 	core.sh: installation functions for the build
	3. 	admin.sh: admin functions for after the build
	4.	install.sh: installation script that uses setting.sh and core.sh (user configurable)

III. Compatibility

	This tool has been configured and tested on the following systems:
	
	1.	Ubuntu 11.10

IV. Usage

	1. 	Download the latest version of the script:

			git://github.com/arcidor/mecury.git

	2. 	Navigate to the script directory
	
	3.	Configure the setting.sh file
	
	4.	Customise the install script (install.sh)
	
	5.	Ensure that the install script is executable:
	
			chmod 700 install.sh
			
	6.	Run the script
	
			./install.sh

V. Notes

	Sections listed in the script as "not implemented" or "placeholder", are
	not required for a normal Ubuntu server installation. These sections may
	be updated in the future, however there is no timeline if place for
	the relevant funtionality.

